diff:1618587174:1618174781:=63,71d62%0a%3c #foxbegin 210416-153255-336840#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!"itself" is used in a similar way %0a%3c -> - Mihir_D%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c "itself" is used very similarly to "only" in Indian English. For example, "I finished my homework today itself". In Standard English this is considered redundant. Redundant language seems to be common in casual speech, as the phrase "return back" is often used as well (instead of just "return" or "come back"). In this case, "itself" could be replaced with "only" as well to have a similar meaning. %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210416-153255-336840#%0a
